Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.63,0:00:09.80,Talk,,0,0,0,,Nos volvemos a ver, ¿eh?{We meet again, huh?}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.46,0:00:14.30,Talk,,0,0,0,,Soy Xiaomei, la narradora de esta historia.{I am Xiaomei, the narrator of this story.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.89,0:00:20.47,Talk,,0,0,0,,Para poder restaurar el verdadero poder del Edens Zero, las cuatro estrellas brillantes son necesarias.{In order to restore the true power of the Edens Zero,\Nthe Four Shining Stars are required.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.98,0:00:24.10,Talk,,0,0,0,,Aquella que supervisó las defensas de la nave, Witch.{The one who oversaw the ship's defenses, Witch.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.60,0:00:28.48,Talk,,0,0,0,,La mal hablada, pero excelente sanadora, Sister.{The foul mouthed but excellent healer, Sister.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.57,0:00:30.90,Talk,,0,0,0,,Ambas ya han sido halladas por Shiki y el resto.{Have been found by Shiki and the others successfully.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.90,0:00:36.07,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y ahora han encontrado a la tercera, Hermit.{And they now found the third, Hermit.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.87,0:00:41.75,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Podrán Shiki y el resto recibirla sin problemas?{Can Shiki and the others safely welcome her?}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.71,0:00:44.37,Talk,,0,0,0,,{Ah.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.25,0:00:48.54,Talk,,0,0,0,,Permitidme disculparme por adelantado.{Allow me to apologize in advance.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.09,0:00:52.80,Talk,,0,0,0,,Veréis, esta historia en particular será extremadamente cruel.{You see, this particular story will be exceedingly sadistic.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.63,0:00:54.84,Talk,,0,0,0,,Lo siento mucho.{I'm very sorry.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.53,0:02:40.36,Title,,0,0,0,,El planeta super virtual{The Super Virtual Planet}
Dialogue: 1,0:02:39.49,0:02:41.12,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡¿Esa es Hermit?!{That's Hermit?!}
Dialogue: 1,0:02:41.20,0:02:42.16,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Increíble!{Amazing!}
Dialogue: 1,0:02:42.24,0:02:43.91,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡La hemos encontrado en nada!{We found her so quickly!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.99,0:02:48.75,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡No me digas que las cuatro estrellas brillantes son todas chicas!{Don't tell me, are all the Four Shining Stars ladies!?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.83,0:02:49.42,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Moscoy!{Moscoy!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.00,0:02:53.13,Talk,,0,0,0,,Para ser precisos, asumo que todas son androides femeninos.{To be precise, \NI assume they are all female-model androids.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.21,0:02:54.52,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Yo soy un gato!{I am a cat-model!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:02:57.76,Talk,,0,0,0,,Le encantaba este sitio.{She always loved it here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.38,0:03:01.80,Talk,,0,0,0,,Así que, ya que pasábamos, me figuré que quizás...{So since we were passing by, I figured maybe-}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.80,0:03:03.51,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Eh?{Hmm?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.22,0:03:07.14,Talk,,0,0,0,,Algo raro le pasa. ¡Subidla a bordo, ya!{Something's wrong with her, \Nget her on board, now!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.22,0:03:07.85,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Moscoy!{Moscoy!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.77,0:03:10.44,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡¿Hermit está bien?!{Is Hermit all right?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.56,0:03:14.27,Talk,,0,0,0,,No se mueve y tampoco ha dicho nada.{She's not moving and she's not saying a word.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.36,0:03:16.90,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Qué le habrá pasado?{Tch. What happened to her?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.98,0:03:20.20,Talk,,0,0,0,,No encuentro daños externos, pero saltan muchos errores del sistema.{I'm not finding any external damage, \Nbut I'm getting way too many error systems.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.28,0:03:22.36,Talk,,0,0,0,,Mi curación no puede hacer nada.{My heal won't do anything against this.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.28,0:03:24.12,Talk,,0,0,0,,Hermit...{Hermit...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.70,0:03:27.33,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿No puedes arreglarla, Weisz?{Can't you fix her, Weisz?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.41,0:03:28.50,Talk,,0,0,0,,No seas idiota.{Don't be crazy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.29,0:03:32.29,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Esa chiquilla es una de las cuatro estrellas brillantes?{A little girl like her is one of the Four Shining Stars...?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.37,0:03:36.50,Talk,,0,0,0,,Es una androide; cómo luzca no importa mucho.{She's an android, \Nwhat she looks like doesn't really reflect much.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.59,0:03:37.55,Talk,,0,0,0,,Moscoy.{Moscoy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.63,0:03:41.38,Talk,,0,0,0,,No hay ningún error en ninguno de sus sistemas de manejo de su reactor de éter.{There's nothing wrong with any of the drive systems in her ether reactor.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.88,0:03:44.47,Talk,,0,0,0,,Funciones del monitor y de sonido sin problemas.{Monitor and sound functions are all normal.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.97,0:03:46.76,Talk,,0,0,0,,Ningún virus detectado.{No viruses detected, either.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.39,0:03:49.18,Talk,,0,0,0,,Un modo de suspensión anormal...{An abnormal sleep mode...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.68,0:03:50.98,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Qué significa eso?{What does that mean?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.56,0:03:54.73,Talk,,0,0,0,,En términos humanos, quiere decir que su corazón ha sido dañado.{In human terms, it means her heart's been damaged.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.81,0:03:56.44,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Su corazón?{Her heart?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.52,0:03:59.78,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Crees que algo terrible le ha podido pasar?{Do you think something scary happened to her?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.86,0:04:01.95,Talk,,0,0,0,,Tanto como para que su corazón se cerrase.{Something terrible enough to make her close her heart.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.32,0:04:03.91,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡¿No hay ningún modo de salvarla?!{Isn't there any way to save her?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.49,0:04:08.41,Talk,,0,0,0,,No tenemos un conocimiento completo del concepto de corazón.{We do not have\N a full understanding of the concept of hearts.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.29,0:04:14.04,Talk,,0,0,0,,No tengo ni idea de cómo arreglar a un androide en estas condiciones.{I don't have the first clue \Nhow to fix an android in this condition.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.75,0:04:16.50,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Tengo una buena idea!{I have a good idea!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.21,0:04:19.17,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡No meteremos dentro de Hermit!{We'll go inside Hermit!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.25,0:04:21.88,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Y entonces arreglaremos su corazón roto!{And then we'll fix her broken heart!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.76,0:04:28.35,Talk,,0,0,0,,Eh... No sé cómo decírtelo...{Um... I don't know where to start with that...}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.85,0:04:31.23,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Cómo se supone que nos meteremos dentro de ella?{How are we supposed to go inside her, again?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.31,0:04:31.93,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Eh?{Eh?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.02,0:04:34.27,Talk,,0,0,0,,Weisz, ¿no puedes hacer una máquina para ello?{Weisz, can't you make a machine for that?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.35,0:04:35.15,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Va a ser que no!{Well, I can't!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.73,0:04:39.32,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Esa clase de "corazón" tiene forma física?{Does this kind of "heart" have a physical shape?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.40,0:04:42.32,Talk,,0,0,0,,Bueno, es un robot, así que puede, ¿o no?{Well, she's a bot, so maybe, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.82,0:04:44.91,Talk,,0,0,0,,Algo claro, con forma de corazón.{Something obvious, like a heart shape.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.99,0:04:45.73,Talk,,0,0,0,,Como que no.{No such thing.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.20,0:04:48.83,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Podrías dejar tus estúpidas ideas de lado?{Would you quit it with your hare brained ideas?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.91,0:04:50.41,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Pero tenemos que salvarla!{But we have to save her somehow!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.25,0:04:55.46,Talk,,0,0,0,,Me siento mal por ella. Tiene el corazón roto...{I feel bad for her, having her heart broken like that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.58,0:04:58.21,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Eh? ¿Vas a llorar?{Oh? You gonna cry?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.29,0:04:59.38,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡No!{I'm not gonna cry!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.46,0:05:01.84,Talk,,0,0,0,,Es muy sentimental, ¿no?{Shiki is surprisingly fragile, isn't he?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.92,0:05:02.97,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡No estoy llorando!{I'm not crying!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.72,0:05:05.63,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Meternos dentro...?{Go inside...?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.85,0:05:09.85,Talk,,0,0,0,,Como era de esperar del gran Rey Demonio.{As expected of the Great Demon King.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.02,0:05:13.02,Talk,,0,0,0,,Puede que haya en modo de salvar a Hermit.{There may be a way to save Hermit.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.10,0:05:14.59,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡¿Te refieres al modo de inmersión?!{You mean dive mode?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.14,0:05:17.31,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Estás diciendo que el corazón de Hermit está...?{So you're saying Hermit's heart is-}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.90,0:05:19.40,Talk,,0,0,0,,En el planeta Digitalis.{On planet Digitalis.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:22.82,Talk,,0,0,0,,Hay una gran posibilidad de que esté ahí.{I have determined a strong possibility that it is there.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.90,0:05:25.20,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Digitalis?\N¿Eh?{-Digitalis?\N-Huh...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:27.11,Talk,,0,0,0,,Entonces, ¿su corazón ni está aquí?{So her heart isn't even here?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.70,0:05:29.63,Talk,,0,0,0,,Está en lo que llamamos "modo de inmersión".{She is currently in what we call "Dive mode".}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.66,0:05:33.91,Talk,,0,0,0,,En este estado, su ego, su espíritu, se ha ido a un mundo digital.{In this state, her ego, \Nher spirit, has gone to a digital world.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.41,0:05:35.25,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Eh?{What?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.33,0:05:37.50,Talk,,0,0,0,,Entonces, es como su hubiera estado soñando todo el tiempo.{So it's like she's been dreaming all this time.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.88,0:05:38.90,Talk,,0,0,0,,Algo así.{Something like that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.25,0:05:43.46,Talk,,0,0,0,,Digitalis es tanto un espacio virtual como un planeta real.{Digitalis is both a virtual space and a real planet.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.96,0:05:45.63,Talk,,0,0,0,,Entonces, es un planeta sin sentido.{So it's a planet that makes no sense.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.26,0:05:49.01,Talk,,0,0,0,,Es un planeta en el que la forma física no influye.{It is a world where the physical body has no influence.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.51,0:05:51.64,Talk,,0,0,0,,El planeta super virtual Digitalis.{The Super Virtual Planet, Digitalis.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.22,0:05:55.02,Talk,,0,0,0,,Si ahí es donde está el corazón de Hermit, ¡vayamos y salvémosla!{If that's where Hermit's heart is, let's go and save her!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.93,0:05:59.23,Talk,,0,0,0,,No se puede acceder a Digitalis con un cuerpo físico.{Digitalis cannot be accessed with a physical body.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.77,0:06:03.40,Talk,,0,0,0,,Tendréis que sumergiros y adquirir formas digitales.{You must all dive, and take digital forms.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.98,0:06:05.65,Talk,,0,0,0,,Suena como un juego en línea.{Sounds like an online game.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.36,0:06:12.45,Talk,,0,0,0,,Digitales comenzó como uno de los servidores de un MMORPG llamado "Rogue Fantasia".{Digitalis started out as one of the servers for an MMORPG called "Rogue Fantasia".}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.95,0:06:15.29,Talk,,0,0,0,,Oí que hubo un incidente hace algunas décadas...{I heard there was an incident a few decades ago...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.37,0:06:18.12,Talk,,0,0,0,,Algo ocurrió y el juego cerró.{Something happened and the game ended service.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.62,0:06:22.63,Talk,,0,0,0,,Sí. Siempre hay riesgos al digitalizar la personalidad de alguien.{Yes. There are the risks that always come from digitizing someone's personality.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.13,0:06:25.88,Talk,,0,0,0,,Los NPC del juego también desarrollaron su propio ego.{The game's NPCs also developed egos of their own.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.38,0:06:27.80,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Que desarrollaron ego?{The NPCs developed egos?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.38,0:06:34.14,Talk,,0,0,0,,Como resultado, el balance del juego fue destruido, se volvió imposible de controlar y, por lo tanto, lo abandonaron.{As a result, the game's balance was destroyed, \Nit became impossible to manage, and so it was abandoned.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.10,0:06:38.39,Talk,,0,0,0,,Tras eso, los NPC reescribieron el código.{After that, the NPCs rewrote the programming.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.48,0:06:41.86,Talk,,0,0,0,,Su sociedad prospera, como si fueran personas reales.{Their society continues to thrive, \Nas if they were real, living people.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.86,0:06:45.65,Talk,,0,0,0,,Entonces, ¿es un planeta de datos de personas?{So it's a planet of data people?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.73,0:06:47.49,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué crees que Hermit estará ahí?{Why do you believe Hermit to be there?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.07,0:06:50.36,Talk,,0,0,0,,Siempre le gustó ese juego.{She always liked that game.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.45,0:06:53.20,Talk,,0,0,0,,Aún es posible entrar en Digitalis.{It is still possible to log into Digitalis.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.83,0:06:58.16,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y confío en los instintos del gran Rey Demonio. ¿Ha respondido eso a tu pregunta?{And I trust the instincts of the Great Demon King. \NDoes that answer your question?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.75,0:07:01.04,Talk,,0,0,0,,Sí. ¡Te prometo que iremos a salvarla!{Yeah. I promise you, we'll go save her!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.83,0:07:06.39,Talk,,0,0,0,,Te ves horrible.{You look awful in that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.39,0:07:07.66,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡La leche! ¡Me va que ni pintado!{It's like I was poured into it! Awesome!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.42,0:07:11.35,Talk,,0,0,0,,Resaltan mucho las curvas...{These suits really emphasize your curves...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.76,0:07:13.35,Talk,,0,0,0,,Son bastante cómodos de vestir.{They are comfortable to wear.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.35,0:07:16.01,Talk,,0,0,0,,Me sorprende que tuvieran de nuestra talla.{I'm surprised they had these in our size.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.01,0:07:17.91,Talk,,0,0,0,,Tal es el poder del la factoría de vestidos.{Such is the power of the Dress Factory.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.59,0:07:06.67,Talk,,0,0,0,,Digitalis es un espacio digital,{Digitalis is a virtual space,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.76,0:07:09.51,Talk,,0,0,0,,así que puedes llegar sin mover la nave.{so you can reach it without moving the ship.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.01,0:07:13.51,Talk,,0,0,0,,Pero no podré crear un respaldo.{However, I will not be able to provide you backup.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.01,0:07:19.39,Talk,,0,0,0,,En cueanto a las habilidades, podréis usar los mismos poderes que en el mundo real, pero nada más.{As for abilities, you will be able to use the same powers you have in the real world, but nothing more.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.48,0:07:22.60,Talk,,0,0,0,,Ah, y una última cosa.{And I must give you a final warning.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.11,0:07:26.90,Talk,,0,0,0,,El daño que recibáis en Digitalis afectará a vuestros cuerpos físicos.{The damage you sustain in Digitalis\N will affect your physical bodies.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.40,0:07:29.19,Talk,,0,0,0,,Si morís en Digitalis...{If you die inside Digitalis-}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.28,0:07:31.07,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Conocemos los riesgos!{We know all about the risks!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.16,0:07:32.78,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Vamos! ¡A encontrar a Hermit!{Let's go! To find Hermit!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.78,0:07:35.58,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Entrando en Digitalis!{Logging you in to Digitalis!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.66,0:07:38.66,Talk,,0,0,0,,Ahora os sumergiréis en el mundo digital.{You will now begin to dive in the digital world.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.83,0:07:44.08,Talk,,0,0,0,,Contamos con vosotros.{We're counting on you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.17,0:07:46.30,Talk,,0,0,0,,O-Ojalá hubiera podido ir con ellos.{I-I wish I could have gone with them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.38,0:07:53.34,Talk,,0,0,0,,Personalice su avatar, por favor.{Please customize your avatar.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.43,0:07:54.68,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡¿Quién anda ahí?!{Who's there?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.76,0:07:57.93,Talk,,0,0,0,,Personalice su avatar, por favor.{Please customize your avatar.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.43,0:08:00.23,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Qué? ¿Es una voz por ordenador?{What, is it a machine voice?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.31,0:08:02.39,Talk,,0,0,0,,Pero ¿qué es un avatar?{But what's an avatar?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.15,0:08:08.57,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡¿Qué cojones?!{What the heck?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.53,0:08:10.40,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Esto es interesante!{This is interesting!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.07,0:08:14.32,Talk,,0,0,0,,No... ¡No es momento para esto!{Oh no... This really isn't the time for this!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.41,0:08:17.20,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Pero es muy divertido! ¡Podría pasarme toda la vida así!{But it's so much fun! \NI could spend my whole life doing it!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.70,0:08:20.16,Test,,0,0,0,,Planeta digitalis{Planet Digitalis}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.49,0:08:20.12,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Guau!{Wow!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.20,0:08:22.36,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Es más fantástico de lo que imaginé!{It's even more fantasy like than I expected!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.67,0:08:24.08,Talk,,0,0,0,,Se parece a Granbell.{It looks like Granbell.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.67,0:08:26.46,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué tardarán tanto?{What's taking everyone so long?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.54,0:08:29.59,Talk,,0,0,0,,Seguro que están complicándose la vida con los avatares.{I bet they're having a hard time making their avatars.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.67,0:08:31.47,Talk,,0,0,0,,Tampoco tiene que ser perfecto.{It's not like it has to be perfect.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.63,0:08:33.93,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Algo viene hacia aquí!{Something's coming this way!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.76,0:08:35.51,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Ah!{Wow!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.85,0:08:41.77,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Algo raro ha aparecido!{Something weird showed up!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.85,0:08:43.77,Talk,,0,0,0,,Espero que los demás lleguen pronto...{I hope the others get here soon...}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.81,0:08:49.11,Talk,,0,0,0,,Uhm... ¿Quién sois?{Uhm, who might you be...?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.19,0:08:50.44,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Deja de mover la cabeza!{Too much face bobbling!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.15,0:08:54.41,Talk,,0,0,0,,Je je... No puedo culparos por no daros cuenta.{Heh heh... I can't blame you for not realizing.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.91,0:09:01.49,Talk,,0,0,0,,Soy un príncipe y espadachín exiliado, que guía a su gente en batalla para recuperar su tierra natal.{I am an exiled prince and swordsman,\N leading my people in battle to restore my motherland.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.29,0:09:05.29,Talk,,0,0,0,,Esos son los ajustes para mí, Homura.{Such is the setting for I, Homura.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.37,0:09:06.67,Talk,,0,0,0,,Uy, lo dije en voz alta.{Oops, I said that aloud.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.75,0:09:07.92,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡¿Homura?!{Homura!?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.00,0:09:10.17,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué te has creado un personaje masculino?{Why did you make a male character?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.25,0:09:12.26,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Eh? Tenía la opción, así que...{Hm? It was an option, so...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.34,0:09:14.01,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Y esto? ¿Qué eso?{And? What's this guy?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.09,0:09:17.55,Talk,,0,0,0,,Traté de seleccionar la opción de "caballo blanco" en la opción de montar, pero...{I had intended to select \Nthe "White horse" option for a mount, but...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.05,0:09:19.01,Talk,,0,0,0,,Es morado...{It's purple...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.56,0:09:20.89,Talk,,0,0,0,,Sí, morado.{Yup, purple.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.97,0:09:22.43,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y no es un caballo...{And it's not a horse...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.52,0:09:26.40,Talk,,0,0,0,,No, de acuerdo con los materiales de ajustes, es un caballo.{No, according to the setting material, it is a horse.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.44,0:09:30.40,Talk,,0,0,0,,El noble corcel que una vez llevó al héroe de las sagradas piedras.{The noble steed who once\N carried the hero of the holy stones.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.48,0:09:31.90,Talk,,0,0,0,,Turn-To-Timonium.{Turn-To-Timonium.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.98,0:09:34.57,Talk,,0,0,0,,Menudo nombrecito.{That's some name.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.65,0:09:35.49,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Y tú quién eres?{And who are you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.07,0:09:37.45,Talk,,0,0,0,,Soy tu hombre, Weisz.{It's your man, Weisz.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.53,0:09:38.70,Talk,,0,0,0,,Quiero decir, ¡tu chica, Weisz!{I mean, your girl, Weisz!}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.20,0:09:41.45,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué te has creado un personaje femenino?{Why did you make a female character?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.54,0:09:44.00,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Eh? Tenía la opción, así que...{What? It was an option, so...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.08,0:09:47.92,Talk,,0,0,0,,Es que mira, ¡puedo tocarlas todo lo que quiera!{I mean, look, I can feel them as much as I want!}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.00,0:09:48.92,Talk,,0,0,0,,Eres lo peor.{You're the worst.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.00,0:09:51.13,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y como las dos somos chicas, podemos ir al baño juntas y...{And since we're both girls, \NI can join you in the bath, and-}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.21,0:09:53.13,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Aún eres un hombre ahí!{You're still a guy in there!}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.21,0:09:56.84,Talk,,0,0,0,,Esto es un espacio virtual. Déjame cumplir algunos sueños.{This is a virtual space.\N Fulfill a few dreams.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.93,0:09:58.30,Talk,,0,0,0,,Qué aburrida.{You're so boring.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.39,0:09:59.68,Talk,,0,0,0,,Eso.{Indeed.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.76,0:10:00.60,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Sí!{Yes!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.68,0:10:02.51,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Yo tengo sueños!{I have dreams!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.14,0:10:07.10,Talk,,0,0,0,,Soy yo, Pino.{It's me, Pino.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.60,0:10:09.48,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Pino?\N¿Humana?{-Pino?\N-Human?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.56,0:10:10.98,Talk,,0,0,0,,Qué monada...{You're so cute~}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.57,0:10:12.57,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Me veo bien?{Do I look all right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.65,0:10:14.32,Talk,,0,0,0,,Sí, ¡te ves genial!{Yeah, you look great!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.40,0:10:16.99,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Bueno! ¡Supongo que ya estamos todos!{Hey! I guess the gang's all here!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.07,0:10:19.20,Talk,,0,0,0,,No podía decidirme, así que cogí mi apariencia de siem...{Couldn't decide my avatar, so I went with my usual loo-}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.24,0:10:20.37,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡¿Apariencia de siempre?!{USUAL LOOK!? HOW?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.45,0:10:22.37,Talk,,0,0,0,,Sí, quería verme un poco más fuerte.{Yeah, I wanted to look a little stronger.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.45,0:10:24.20,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Eso es más que un poco!{THAT'S MORE THAN A LITTLE!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.25,0:10:26.21,Talk,,0,0,0,,Sí que parece fuerte.{He does look strong.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.96,0:10:31.88,Talk,,0,0,0,,Como este sitio se parece un poco a Granbell,{Since this place is a little like Granbell,}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.96,0:10:34.55,Talk,,0,0,0,,pensé que podría ponerme el pelo como lo tenía entonces.{I thought I'd give myself\N the hair I had when I lived there.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.63,0:10:38.13,Talk,,0,0,0,,Ah, qué recuerdos...{Ah, the memories...}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.13,0:10:42.14,Talk,,0,0,0,,Espero que todos... regresasen a la normalidad...{I hope everyone... made it back to normal...}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.70,0:10:43.72,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡No llores!{Don't cry!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.89,0:10:47.64,Talk,,0,0,0,,Este mundo en principio era un videojuego,{This world was originally a video game,}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.14,0:10:52.40,Talk,,0,0,0,,pero quisieron hacerlo lo más realista posible, así que casi no hay HUD.{but they wanted it to be as realistic as possible, so there's almost no HUD.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.40,0:10:54.94,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿HUD?{HUD?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.03,0:10:56.74,Talk,,0,0,0,,Head-up display.{Head-up display.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.82,0:11:00.16,Talk,,0,0,0,,Las cosas que siempre aparecen en pantalla cuando juegas.{The things you always see on the screen when you're playing video games.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.24,0:11:02.03,Talk,,0,0,0,,Así que no hay lo normal de los RPG...{So no RPG classics-}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.53,0:11:04.91,Talk,,0,0,0,,La barra de estado del HP y demás.{The status display for HP and all that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.99,0:11:06.70,Talk,,0,0,0,,Se carga un poco el ambiente.{Kinda kills the mood.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.79,0:11:08.46,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Quieres que le dé un pequeño arreglillo?{Want me to fix it a little?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.16,0:11:10.12,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡No!{NO!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.83,0:11:14.92,Talk,,0,0,0,,En este planeta podemos usar todas nuestras habilidades del mundo real.{On this planet, we can use all our real world abilities.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.42,0:11:17.05,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Ah, es verdad!{Oooh! You're right!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.13,0:11:20.93,Talk,,0,0,0,,Pero reescribir el código del planeta es algo que tenemos que evitar.{But rewriting the planet's data is one thing we have to avoid.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.51,0:11:26.52,Talk,,0,0,0,,Entonces, el Machina Maker y mi PEM van en contra de las reglas.{So Machina Maker and my EMP are against the rules.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.60,0:11:27.27,Talk,,0,0,0,,Entendido.{Understood.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.35,0:11:29.64,Talk,,0,0,0,,Entiendes que entonces no tiene sentido que estemos aquí, ¿no?{You realize there's\N no point in us being here then, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.73,0:11:31.85,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Y qué pasa cuando rompemos las reglas?{And what happens when we break the rules?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.94,0:11:36.23,Talk,,0,0,0,,Se llama "ban". Te echan del mundo y no puedes volver.{It's called a "ban". You get kicked out of the world and can never come back again.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.19,0:11:40.15,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Ey, mirad! ¡Hay un pueblo cerca!{Hey, look! There's a town nearby!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.24,0:11:42.66,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Apuesto que ahí es donde comienza nuestra aventura!{I bet that's where our adventure begins!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.16,0:11:47.08,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Vamos a ser héroes! ¡A salvar a Hermit!{We're going to be heroes! To save Hermit!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.99,0:11:49.33,Talk,,0,0,0,,Pero ya eres un Rey Demonio.{But you're already a Demon King.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.79,0:11:54.29,Test,,0,0,0,,Drimille
Dialogue: 1,0:11:53.29,0:11:56.13,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Increíble! ¡Es un pueblo real!{This is amazing! It's like a real town!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.21,0:11:57.96,Talk,,0,0,0,,Vaya, qué realista.{Wow, total realism.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.67,0:12:02.22,Talk,,0,0,0,,Mira, ahí hay otro Turn-To-Timonium.{Look, I see another Turn-To-Timonium over there.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.72,0:12:05.01,Talk,,0,0,0,,Parece que Tantimo, para acortar.{Apparently, they're Tantimo for short.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.10,0:12:07.14,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Sois viajeros?{Are you travelers?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.22,0:12:10.48,Talk,,0,0,0,,Bienvenido a Drimille, el pueblo de la vegetación.{Welcome to Drimille, the town of greenery.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.56,0:12:11.27,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Buenas!{Yo!}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.35,0:12:12.98,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Es un NPC?{Is he an NPC?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.06,0:12:16.44,Talk,,0,0,0,,Bueno, dijeron que los NPC de aquí son conscientes de ellos mismos.{Well, they did say the NPCs here are self-aware.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.02,0:12:20.65,Talk,,0,0,0,,Me alegra ver que se han unido tantos jugadores últimamente.{I'm so happy to see that we've been getting so many more players lately.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.82,0:12:22.70,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Jugadores?{Players?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.78,0:12:24.99,Talk,,0,0,0,,Gente como vosotros.{People like you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.07,0:12:28.54,Talk,,0,0,0,,Los que vienen aquí desde el mundo exterior son jugadores.{People who dive here from the outside world are players.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.62,0:12:31.00,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y nosotros, que vivimos en este planeta,{And people like us, who live on this planet,}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.08,0:12:32.83,Talk,,0,0,0,,somos NPC.{are called NPCs.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.21,0:12:39.88,Talk,,0,0,0,,Claro que los NPC de aquí hacemos más cosas de los que el juego nos asignó originalmente.{Of course, the NPCs here do more than the jobs the game originally assigned to us.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.96,0:12:40.71,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Originalmente?{Originally?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.38,0:12:44.26,Talk,,0,0,0,,Antes, solo podía decir la misma línea una y otra vez{Before,I could only ever \Nsay the same line over and over,}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.26,0:12:49.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,¿Eres un viajero? Bienvenido a Drimille, el pueblo de la vegetación.{Are you a traveller? \NWelcome to Drimille,\N the town of greenery.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.34,0:12:46.30,Talk,,0,0,0,,debido a mi programación.{ because of my programming,}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.39,0:12:49.22,Talk,,0,0,0,,Era un infierno.{It was hell.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.81,0:12:51.85,Talk,,0,0,0,,A veces, cuando un jugador desencadenaba ciertas banderas,{Sometimes, after a player triggered certain flags,}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.93,0:12:54.27,Talk,,0,0,0,,podía decirles una línea diferente.{I could say a different line to them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.35,0:12:55.81,Talk,,0,0,0,,Tienes mi apoyo.{You have my sympathies.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.90,0:12:58.32,Talk,,0,0,0,,Buscamos a alguien.{We're looking for someone.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.82,0:13:00.82,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Conoces a alguien llamada Hermit?{Do you know anyone named Hermit?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.90,0:13:02.53,Talk,,0,0,0,,No puedo decir que la conozca.{Can't say that I do.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.61,0:13:06.41,Talk,,0,0,0,,Pero es un pueblo grande. Quizás alguien la conozca.{But it's a big town. \NSomeone might be familiar with that person.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.49,0:13:07.95,Talk,,0,0,0,,Preguntad por el pueblo.{Ask around town.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.03,0:13:11.54,Talk,,0,0,0,,A todos nos encanta hablar.{We all love talking.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.12,0:13:13.91,Talk,,0,0,0,,De verdad actúa como si estuviera vivo.{He really does act like he's alive.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.42,0:13:16.50,Talk,,0,0,0,,No me puedo creer que no sea más que datos.{I can't believe that's just data.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.58,0:13:19.21,Talk,,0,0,0,,Apuesto que la gente de aquí también tiene corazón.{I bet the folks here have hearts, too.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.92,0:13:21.67,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Qué ocurre, Srta. Homura?{What's the matter, Miss Homura?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.26,0:13:23.84,Talk,,0,0,0,,Quizás es demasiado realista.{Maybe it's too realistic.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.92,0:13:26.68,Talk,,0,0,0,,No dificultará distinguir a jugadores de NPC.{It will render us unable to distinguish players from NPC.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.76,0:13:30.14,Talk,,0,0,0,,Sí, sería fácil para uno hacerse pasar como el otro.{Yeah, it would be easy for one to pretend to be the other.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.72,0:13:33.52,Talk,,0,0,0,,Dijo que habían estado llegando más jugadores, ¿no?{He said they'd been getting more players lately, didn't he?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.60,0:13:35.23,Talk,,0,0,0,,Hice una pequeña búsqueda antes de venir.{I did some research before we got here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.31,0:13:37.52,Talk,,0,0,0,,Aún quedan muchos jugadores.{There's still a fair amount of players left.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.40,0:13:43.07,Talk,,0,0,0,,En otras palabras: puede que nos encontremos con jugadores con intenciones no muy honorables hacia la gente de aquí.{In other words, we might find players with less than honorable intentions among the people here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.65,0:13:45.36,Talk,,0,0,0,,Deberemos mantener una vigilancia constante.{We must maintain constant vigilance.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.95,0:13:46.45,Talk,,0,0,0,,Sí.{Yeah.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.95,0:13:50.03,Talk,,0,0,0,,Como sea, buscamos información acerca de Hermit.{Anyway, we're looking for info on Hermit.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.53,0:13:52.20,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Separémonos y preguntemos por la ciudad!{Let's all split up and ask around town!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.10,0:14:18.85,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Y? ¿Qué hemos descubierto?{So? What did we find out?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.31,0:14:23.82,Talk,,0,0,0,,"Puede que la haya visto en un pueblo del norte". Eso es todo lo que sabemos.{"I may have seen her in a town in the north."\NThat is all we know.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.40,0:14:26.70,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Nos hemos paseado por toda la ciudad y solo tenemos eso?{We walked through the whole town and that's all we got?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.78,0:14:28.48,Talk,,0,0,0,,No es información muy fiable.{It's not very reliable information.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.86,0:14:30.99,Talk,,0,0,0,,Como sea, ¡mañana nos vamos al norte!{Anyway, tomorrow, we head north!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.66,0:14:32.91,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Por ahora a dormir!{Tonight, we sleep!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.99,0:14:34.79,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Qué? ¿No nos vamos a desconectar?{What? We're not logging out?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.87,0:14:36.96,Talk,,0,0,0,,Bueno, no pasará nada por una noche.{Well, one night should be okay.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:41.50,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Rebeca! ¿Te vienes al baño conmigo?{Oh Beckyyyyyyyyy~ \NWould you like to join me in the bath?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.59,0:14:42.71,Talk,,0,0,0,,Qué miedo.{You're scaring me!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.79,0:14:44.71,Test,,0,0,0,,Crysta
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.88,0:14:50.26,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Hola! ¡Bienvenido a la posada de los aventureros!{Hello! Welcome to the travelers' inn!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.34,0:14:51.56,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Vas a pasar la noche?{Will you be staying the night?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.89,0:14:53.68,Talk,,0,0,0,,Quiero una mujer.{I want a woman.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.68,0:14:57.98,Talk,,0,0,0,,Este no es esa clase de establecimien...{T-This isn't that kind of establish-}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.06,0:14:59.52,Talk,,0,0,0,,{Eek!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.10,0:15:03.19,Talk,,0,0,0,,La nueva mujer... Sé que está aquí.{The new woman... I know she's here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.27,0:15:04.86,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡P-Para!{S-stop that!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.94,0:15:08.03,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Atacar a los NPC va en contra de las reglas!{Attacking NPCs is against the rules!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.11,0:15:12.03,Talk,,0,0,0,,Puedo matar a un NPC y aun así no ser baneado.{I can kill an NPC and still not get banned.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.12,0:15:15.54,Talk,,0,0,0,,Porque soy un jugador elegido.{'Cause  I'm a chosen player.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.21,0:15:24.09,Talk,,0,0,0,,Hermit... ¿Por qué cerrarías tu corazón?{Hermit... \NWhy would you close your heart?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.59,0:15:26.26,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Qué narices te pasó?{What in the Cosmos happened to you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.21,0:15:28.34,Talk,,0,0,0,,Witch.{Witch.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.47,0:15:32.51,Talk,,0,0,0,,Hay información extraña tratando de colarse.{We got some strange data trying to blend in.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.51,0:15:35.18,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Hacking?\N¿Moscoy?{-Hacking?\N-Moscoy?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.76,0:15:38.73,Talk,,0,0,0,,Pero la seguridad del Edens Zero debería estar perfecta.{But Edens Zero's security should be perfect.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.23,0:15:41.90,Talk,,0,0,0,,Es de cuando metimos a Hermit.{It is... When we have Hermit.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.60,0:15:46.19,Talk,,0,0,0,,No sé qué estará haciendo, pero no podemos dejar que revolotee tan tranquilo.{I don't know what it's doing there,\N but we can't let it stick around.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.98,0:15:50.11,Talk,,0,0,0,,O puede que dañe a nuestro equipo en Digitalis.{Or it might hurt our team down in Digitalis.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.58,0:15:57.70,Talk,,0,0,0,,Sabes, me gusta este escenario.{You know, I kinda like this scenery.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.79,0:16:00.41,Talk,,0,0,0,,Te hace sentir como estuvieras en un mundo de fantasía.{It really makes you feel like you're in a fantasy world.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.00,0:16:04.96,Talk,,0,0,0,,Aun así, me sorprende que podamos oler y saborear en un mundo virtual.{Even so, I am astounded\N to experience taste and smell in a virtual world.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.46,0:16:08.38,Talk,,0,0,0,,Solo demuestra lo mucho que se han esforzado en hacerlo.{It just goes to show how much reality they put into making it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.46,0:16:12.26,Talk,,0,0,0,,Ahora solo necesitanos un monstruo que nos bloquee el camino.{Now all we need is some kinda monster to block our path.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.34,0:16:12.84,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Eh?{Hmm?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.39,0:16:16.93,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Ah!\N¡Tenías que abrir la boca!{-Eek~!  \N-You had to go and jinx us!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.01,0:16:18.35,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Aquí está!{Here it is!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.93,0:16:21.39,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Había chicos como él en Granbell!{We had guys just like him in Granbell!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.48,0:16:23.06,Talk,,0,0,0,,Pero claro, ¡esos eran bots!{But of course, those were bots!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.15,0:16:26.32,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y nunca tuvimos visitas, ¡así que nunca tuvieron nada que hacer!{And we never had any guests, \Nso they never had anything to do!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.40,0:16:28.48,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Los chicos de aquí tienen mucha suerte!{The guys here are really lucky!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.57,0:16:30.69,Talk,,0,0,0,,Puedo darle una buena patada en el culo, ¿no?{I can just kick its butt, right?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.78,0:16:31.61,Talk,,0,0,0,,No veo por qué no.{I don't see why not.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.53,0:16:34.03,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Allá voy!{Here goes!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.11,0:16:37.24,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡E-Esperen, se lo imploro, buenos viajeros!{W-Waiteth, I implore you, good travelers!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.33,0:16:38.91,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Ha hablado!{It talks!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.58,0:16:43.00,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡N-No soy un monstruo malo, oigan!{I-I ain't a bad monster-eth!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.08,0:16:43.71,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Oigan?{-Eth...?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.79,0:16:45.54,Talk,,0,0,0,,No... Esperen.{No... Wait-eth a second.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.63,0:16:48.84,Talk,,0,0,0,,Técnicamente soy el jefe de un evento, así que supongo que sí soy un tipo malo.{I am technically an event boss, \Nso I guess-eth I am a bad guy?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.34,0:16:52.51,Talk,,0,0,0,,Hay un pueblo al norte llamado Crysta.{There's a town north of here called Crysta.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.59,0:16:56.68,Talk,,0,0,0,,Ahí pueden activar una {\i1}quest{\i0}, que consiste en recuperar el tesoro secreto del pueblo{You can activate-eth a quest there, called retrieve the town's secret treasure.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.01,0:17:04.19,Talk,,0,0,0,,En su búsqueda del tesoro secreto, los aventureros casualmente encuentran mi humilde cueva peleando.{In their search for the secret treasure, the adventurers eventually reach-eth my humble cave dwelling.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.73,0:17:12.36,Talk,,0,0,0,,Pero en realidad, era una profunda historia en la que he estado usando el tesoro para proteger a la gente del pueblo.{But in reality... It was-eth a touching story where I had been using-eth the treasure to protect the townspeople.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.90,0:17:15.11,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Ah! ¡He soltado unos buenos {\i1}spoilers{\i0}!{AH! I'M GIVETH AWAY SPOILERS!}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.20,0:17:16.95,Talk,,0,0,0,,Está bien. No nos importa.{That's okay, we don't care.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.79,0:17:20.95,Talk,,0,0,0,,Ahora está enfurruñado.{Now he's sulking.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.04,0:17:23.16,Talk,,0,0,0,,Bueno, como si me importase.{Well, I really don't care.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.25,0:17:26.75,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y ¿qué estás haciendo aquí, señor jefe del evento?{So what are you doing here, mister event boss?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.33,0:17:27.88,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Sí!{Right!}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.96,0:17:31.88,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡El pueblo al norte, Crysta! ¡Está en problemas!{The town-eth in the north, Crysta! \NIt's in big trouble-eth!}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.55,0:17:35.84,Talk,,0,0,0,,He oído rumores... Y ahora sé que son ciertos.{I'd heard the rumors... \NAnd now I know they were true.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.93,0:17:36.84,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Cierto el qué?{What's true?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.93,0:17:39.56,Talk,,0,0,0,,El asesino de masas Jamilov.{It's the mass murderer Jamilov.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.64,0:17:42.06,Talk,,0,0,0,,Ha aparecido en Crysta.{He has appeared-eth in Crysta.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.64,0:17:43.81,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Asesino de masas?{Mass murderer?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.89,0:17:45.52,Talk,,0,0,0,,Un apodo amenazante.{An ominous nickname.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.10,0:17:50.52,Talk,,0,0,0,,No le importa matar a NPC o jugadores... Arrasa con todos.{He doesn't care if he kills players or NPCs... \NHe kills everyone.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.61,0:17:52.03,Talk,,0,0,0,,Es muy malvado.{He is unbelievably evil-eth.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.11,0:17:53.99,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Y él también es un jugador?{And is he a player, too?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.57,0:17:58.32,Talk,,0,0,0,,Pero, si está matando NPC, ¿no debería ser baneado?{But if he's killing NPCs, shouldn't he get banned?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.41,0:18:01.58,Talk,,0,0,0,,Sí, pero por alguna razón, el ban nunca llega.{Yes, but for some reason, the ban never come-eth.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.16,0:18:05.54,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Y ahora Crysta está hecha escombros!{And now Crysta is a total disaster area-eth!}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.62,0:18:08.54,Talk,,0,0,0,,Los jugadores y NPC han sido asesinados...{Now the players and NPCs have been murdered...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.63,0:18:10.59,Talk,,0,0,0,,y las banderas de eventos están desordenadas...{And the event flags are a mess...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.17,0:18:14.17,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y entonces, fui forzado a correr por mi vida.{And so, I was forced-eth to run for my life.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.47,0:18:20.80,Talk,,0,0,0,,Buscamos a alguien del pueblo del norte; una chica llamada Hermit.{We're looking for someone in the north town. \NA girl named Hermit.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.31,0:18:23.22,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿La conoces?{Do you know her?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.31,0:18:26.94,Talk,,0,0,0,,Hermit... ¿Os referís a la jugadora que se queda mirando al espacio?{Hermit...\N You mean the player who stares into space?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.02,0:18:27.81,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡La conoces!{You do know her!}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.90,0:18:29.94,Talk,,0,0,0,,Nunca completa ningún evento.{She never completes any events.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.02,0:18:32.94,Talk,,0,0,0,,Solo se sienta aturdida, en una colina a las afueras del pueblo.{Just sits there in a daze-eth.\N On the hill just outside town.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.03,0:18:34.57,Talk,,0,0,0,,La he visto a menudo.{I've seen-eth her often.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.65,0:18:35.49,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Ya veo!{I see!}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.57,0:18:37.20,Talk,,0,0,0,,Entonces, ¡Hermit está aquí!{So Hermit really is here!}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.82,0:18:39.82,Talk,,0,0,0,,Muchas gracias, señor monstruo.{Thank you very much, Mister Monster.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.62,0:18:43.83,Talk,,0,0,0,,Mejor apresurémonos, que hay un rarito cerca.{We better hurry\N if there's some weirdo wandering around.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.91,0:18:44.58,Talk,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Aye!{\i0}{Aye!}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.66,0:18:48.04,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡¿Se van a Crysta?!{A-Are you guys going-eth to Crysta?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.62,0:18:50.17,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Vamos a por un miembro de nuestro grupo!{We're going to get a member of our crew!}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.25,0:18:52.50,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡No importa donde sea que esté!{It doesn't matter what kind of place she's in!}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.09,0:18:54.21,Talk,,0,0,0,,{Ah…}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.76,0:18:59.34,Talk,,0,0,0,,Qué horror...{This is awful...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.43,0:19:01.26,Talk,,0,0,0,,Parece que no hay nadie aquí.{There appears to be no one here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.85,0:19:04.01,Talk,,0,0,0,,No, ahí hay alguien.{No, over there. I see somebody.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.60,0:19:06.85,Talk,,0,0,0,,Bienvenidos...{Welcome.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.93,0:19:09.56,Talk,,0,0,0,,a Crysta, la preciosa ciudad de los cristales.{To Crysta, the beautiful city of crystals.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.60,0:19:11.98,Talk,,0,0,0,,Bienvenidos...{Welcome.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.69,0:19:15.99,Talk,,0,0,0,,a Crysta, la preciosa ciudad de los cristales.{To Crysta, the beautiful city of crystals.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.07,0:19:17.99,Talk,,0,0,0,,Bien... venidos...{Wel... come.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.53,0:19:22.87,Talk,,0,0,0,,Estos NPC no me sirven.{These NPCs really don't do it for me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.95,0:19:26.66,Talk,,0,0,0,,Al final, no son más que programas.{In the end, you can always\N tell they're just programs.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.16,0:19:29.00,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡No me sirven!{They really don't do it for me!}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.17,0:19:33.92,Talk,,0,0,0,,Parece que los jugadores son lo único que merece la pena cazar.{Guess players are the only ones worth hunting after all.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.17,0:19:35.67,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Verdad?{Right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.96,0:19:38.63,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Mis queridos amigos jugadores?{My dear player friends?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.43,0:19:42.64,Talk,,0,0,0,,No me digas que es el tipo de los rumores...{Don't tell me he's the guy in the rumors...}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.72,0:19:44.05,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡El asesino de masas!{The mass murderer!}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.14,0:19:46.18,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Podrías escucharme un momentín?{Would you listen to this?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.27,0:19:49.35,Talk,,0,0,0,,He oído que había nuevos jugadores en Digitalis.{I heard there were some new players in Digitalis.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.94,0:19:53.56,Talk,,0,0,0,,Así que pensé en pasarme a decir hola, pero me confundí de pueblo.{So I thought I'd say hello, but I got the wrong town.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.65,0:19:55.73,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Menudo problemón!{It's the worst!}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.23,0:20:00.28,Talk,,0,0,0,,Estaban en esta posada, con un grupo de enormes gorilas veteranos.{There I was at this inn,\N with a party of big hulking veteran gorillas.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.36,0:20:03.66,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y  pasa que no me van los tíos ni los gorilas.{And the thing is, I'm not into dudes or gorillas.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.74,0:20:06.04,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡No me sirven, para nada!{They really don't do it for me!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.12,0:20:08.75,Talk,,0,0,0,,Así que... Ya sabéis. ¡Mirad!{So I just... You know.\NTake a look!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.41,0:20:12.17,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Véis? Ahí están.{See? They're over there!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.17,0:20:21.05,Talk,,0,0,0,,Ah... A-Ayuda...{Ah... ah... help me...}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.13,0:20:22.30,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Siguen vivos!{They're still alive!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.38,0:20:23.59,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Mierda!{Shit!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.43,0:20:30.18,Talk,,0,0,0,,De todos modos, no los podréis salvar.{You won't be able to save them, anyway.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.81,0:20:34.90,Talk,,0,0,0,,Mis poderes no les dejan desconectarse.{My powers are keeping them from logging out.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.98,0:20:39.69,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y aunque pudieran, ya es demasiado tarde como para ayudarlos en el mundo real.{And even if they could log out, it's too late to help them in the real world.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.28,0:20:40.90,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Cabrón!{You bastard!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.99,0:20:44.49,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y si les dejo desconectarse, ¡no podría ver sus momentos finales!{If I let them log out, I couldn't see their final moments!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.57,0:20:46.37,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Eso no me serviría, para nada!{That really wouldn't do it for me!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.83,0:20:50.95,Talk,,0,0,0,,Están muertos...{They're dead...}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.25,0:20:57.67,Talk,,0,0,0,,Y ahora, no me he presentado.{Now then. I haven't introduced myself.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.75,0:21:00.59,Talk,,0,0,0,,Soy Jamilov, el jugador elegido.{I am Jamilov. The chosen player.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.34,0:21:02.95,Talk,,0,0,0,,Soy de los ganadores, aquí y en la vida real.{I am one of the winners, here and IRL.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.97,0:21:05.39,Talk,,0,0,0,,Trabajo con Drakken Joe.{I work with THE Drakken Joe.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.43,0:21:08.81,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Drakken Joe?{Drakken Joe?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.89,0:21:09.72,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Le conoces?{You know him?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.31,0:21:11.85,Talk,,0,0,0,,Oración Seis Galactica.{Oracion Seis Galactica.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.35,0:21:15.27,Talk,,0,0,0,,Uno de seis guerreros que se dice que han destruido planetas enteros.{One of six warriors \Nwho are said to have crushed entire planets.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.81,0:21:17.69,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Q-Qué dices?{Wh-what are you saying?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.27,0:21:20.32,Talk,,0,0,0,,¿Estáis asustados? ¡Pues claro que sí!{Are you scared? Of course you are!}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.40,0:21:23.86,Talk,,0,0,0,,¡Me encanta! ¡En especial esa mirada en la cara de una mujer!{I love it! Especially that kinda look on a woman's face!}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.95,0:21:26.24,Talk,,0,0,0,,No me importa con quién trabajes.{I don't care who you work with.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.87,0:21:29.70,Talk,,0,0,0,,No te irás de rositas.{You won't get away with this.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.21,0:21:37.46,Talk,,0,0,0,,Ziggy, eres un mentiroso.{Ziggy. You're a liar.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.42,0:21:40.63,Talk,,0,0,0,,Puede que las máquinas sí tengan corazones...,{Maybe machines do have hearts...}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.63,0:21:44.51,Talk,,0,0,0,,pero los humanos no.{...but humans don't.}
